cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it proposes a topology visualisation tool for large-scale complex networks such as the Internet and peer-to-peer (P2P) networks. It may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the study of complex network structures. Additionally, it could be categorised under cs.SD (Software Development) as it proposes a tool for visualising network structures. It may also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves the sorting of network nodes. Finally, it could be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it deals with the representation and visualisation of information in complex networks.
